  "title": "Writing as Method",
  "abstract": "Writing as a method of inquiry refers to a research practice of foregrounding and investigating how researchers construct knowledge about people, themselves, and the world by writing. This concept, introduced by Laurel Richardson (2000 [1994]) and developed by Elizabeth St. Pierre (Richardson and St. Pierre, 2005) and others, brings the idea that writing is thinking from the humanities to the social sciences.",
